Subject: RE: [VB] bent crankshaft pully.

Josh, if your engine is already out you can take the large screwdriver
you use to pull the oil pressure relief piston screws out with and
evenly tap with a mallet on both sides at the hub until it works loose.
I wouldn't under any circumstances used a warped pulley for numerous
reasons.

